  "text": "then, we consider p as a candidate feature point, t is a given threshold value, I x is the gray value of the sequential n pixel, and I p is the gray value of pixel p, [CITATION_1] . For features extraction and descriptors computation in the first and second hybrid combinations based on using F AST , the Binary Robust Invariant Scalable Keypoints (BRISK) algorithm is incorporated, [CITATION_2] , because F AST can only detect corner features but dose not compute the descriptors. Therefore, this paper uses BRISK descriptor with F AST keypoints.",
